dataIdInfo.idPurp:
This dataset symbolizes the voting areas for the 2023 Manitoba General Election in their draft form. This is the product of the VA redistricting process, with the intention of being used in the draft maps for the mapping assignment. Once the mapping assignment is complete, VAs will be finalized a new feature class will be created with the voting areas in their final form for the 2023 election.
Current Status Aug 08, 2022 The voting areas for all Winnipeg EDs have been created and added to the feature class. The VAs in Headingley (Roblin ED) and West St. Paul (McPhillips ED) still need to be redistricted and finalized. For now, the 2019 VAs are serving as placeholders and have a VANUM = 0. The VAs in this layer will be updated once rural redistricting has been completed.
